data.enText: a person whose job is to drive a car, especially for sb rich or important
to drive sb in a car, usually as your job

data.chText: 他由司机开车送去参加所有的会议。
data.enText: He was chauffeured to all his meetings.

data.chText: 有专职司机驾驶的豪华轿车

tr: a man paid to drive a privately owned car

value.def: The chauffeur of a rich or important person is the man or woman who is employed to look after their car and drive them around in it.
If you chauffeur someone somewhere, you drive them there in a car, usually as part of your job.

example.ex: It was certainly useful to have her there to chauffeur him around...
example.tran: 有她在那儿还是挺有用的，能开车带他到处跑。

example.ex: Caroline had a chauffeured car waiting to take her to London.
example.tran: 卡罗琳有辆配有司机的轿车，随时准备送她去伦敦。
